==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tremor
<hw>Tre"mor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., from
<ets>tremere</ets> to tremble. See <er>Tremble</er>,
<pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <def>A trembling; a shivering or shaking; a
quivering or vibratory motion; <as>as, the <ex>tremor</ex> of a person
who is weak, infirm, or old</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He fell into an universal <qex>tremor</qex> of all his joints.</q>
<rj><qau>Harvey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tremulent</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Tremulant</ent>⟦br⟧
